title: For Sale:  Egyptian Hakim, 8MM Mauser Semi-Auto with Full Choke -- Nice!
postcontent: Hi!  Thanks for looking!For sale today, we have a beautiful Egyptian Hakim.  This is a semi-automatic rifle chambered in the legendary 8MM Mauser.  These rifles were designed for Egypt by Sweden in order to take advantage of their large stockpiles of 8MM Mauser, a fast, accurate round.  Featuring a full choke, this rifle exhibits almost no kick.One of the most unusual actions, the dust cover is slid back by the user, and it automatically chambers a round with a powerful spring-loaded action.  A unique tilt-over feed option is designed in to allow the user to feed two 5-round stripper clips into the detachable 10-round box magazine.An aftermarket modified MG13 25-round magazine is available online, usually for around $100.This is an attention-hog.  Most times I take it to the range, someone comes up to say, "What on earth is that?"  Perhaps it's because the big Mauser round going through a full choke makes a blast like a nearby hand grenade.Money is tight, and I hate to let this one go as I have so much fun shooting it.  However, I'm not taking any offers below the asking price at this time.  Thanks again for looking, and if you have any questions, please feel free to ask!  (-:(Notes: This listing's Manufacturer is "Mauser" for search-feature reasons.)
